.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
The dialog widget handles a whole screen. 
.PP
.SH "Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "\fBsgWidget\fP * sgNewDialog (SDL_Surface * screen, \fBsgWidgetProc\fP * proc, Uint16 border, Uint8 alpha, \fBsgColor\fP color, int fps)"
.PP
Create a dialog. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIscreen\fP The screen surface the dialog will be drawn to 
.br
\fIproc\fP Procedure that handles events of the dialog and all its children 
.br
\fIborder\fP Default border for any child widget 
.br
\fIalpha\fP Default alpha for any child widget 
.br
\fIcolor\fP Default color for any child widget 
.br
\fIfps\fP FPS rate at which the dialog should be displayed
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns:\fP
.RS 4
A dialog widget
.RE
.PP

.SS "void sgSetDialogTimer (\fBsgWidget\fP * dialog, \fBsgDialogTimer\fP * fn, Uint32 interval, void * arg)"
.PP
Sets a timer callback for the dialog which is run periodically from \fBsgRunDialog()\fP. 
.PP
\fBParameters:\fP
.RS 4
\fIdialog\fP the dialog that will run the timer 
.br
\fIfn\fP callback function which is periodically called (has widget as first argument) 
.br
\fIinterval\fP time between timer calls in milliseconds 
.br
\fIarg\fP is passed to the callback as second argument
.RE
.PP

